&nbsp;Faf du Plessis has been found guilty of ball-tampering and fined his entire match fee from the second test against Australia in Hobart but the South Africa captain has been cleared to play in this week&#8217;s third and final match of the series.Du Plessis received the punishment following an International Cricket Council (ICC) hearing in Adelaide on Tuesday, two days ahead of South Africa&#8217;s first day-night test match at the Adelaide Oval.-Reuters